<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
Pileus 1.6-4.4 cm in diam. Context white, greyish-brown when moist. Basidiospores 9.5-12.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.9-9.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. The ITS sequence of the holotype differs from other species in section 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Fuscoperonati">Fuscoperonati</taxonomicName>
by at least six substitutions and six indels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
