<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. Li &amp; M. L. Xie" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subfuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corresponds well to the characteristics of section 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Fuscoperonati">Fuscoperonati</taxonomicName>
, with weak hygrophanous pileus, an annular band on the middle stipe and distinct belts or zones lower down, large spores (&gt; 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long) and grow in coniferous forests. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhner" authorityYear="1953" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius fuscoperonatus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius fuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously placed in section 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="section" section="Bovini">Bovini</taxonomicName>
M.M. Moser (
<bibRefCitation author="Bidaud, A" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B6" refString="Bidaud, A, Moenne-Loccoz, P, Reumaux, P, Carteret, X, 2009. Atlas des Cortinaires XVIII. Editions Federation Mycologique Dauphine-Savoie, Meyzieu." title="Atlas des Cortinaires XVIII. Editions Federation Mycologique Dauphine-Savoie, Meyzieu." year="2009">Bidaud et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soop, K" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B50" refString="Soop, K, 2014. Cortinarius in Sweden (14 edition). Editions Scientrixk, Sweden." title="Cortinarius in Sweden (14 edition). Editions Scientrixk, Sweden." year="2014">Soop 2014</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="M.M.Moser" authorityName="M.M.Moser" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Armillati" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Armillati" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Armillati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brandrud, TE" journalOrPublisher="Agarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B12" refString="Brandrud, TE, Lindstroem, H, Marklund, H, Melot, J, Muskos, S, 1992. Cortinarius Flora Photographica II. Cortinarius HB, Matfors." title="Cortinarius Flora Photographica II. Cortinarius HB, Matfors." year="1992">Brandrud et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
), until 
<bibRefCitation author="Niskanen, T" journalOrPublisher="Index Fungorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 2" publicationUrl="http://www.indexfungorum.org/Publications/Index%20Fungorum%20no.256.pdf" refId="B38" refString="Niskanen, T, Kytoevuori, I, Liimatainen, K, Ammirati, JF, 2015. Nomenclatural novelties. Index Fungorum 256: 1 - 2, http://www.indexfungorum.org/Publications/Index%20Fungorum%20no.256.pdf" title="Nomenclatural novelties." url="http://www.indexfungorum.org/Publications/Index%20Fungorum%20no.256.pdf" volume="256" year="2015">Niskanen et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
placed it in section 
<taxonomicName authority="M.M.Moser" authorityName="M.M.Moser" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Armillati" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Fuscoperonati">Fuscoperonati</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. Li &amp; M. L. Xie" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subfuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cortinarius subfuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has remarkably similar morphological characteristics to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fuscoperonatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="fuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. fuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, apart from the spores of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fuscoperonatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="fuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. fuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being narrower (9.7-11.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.6-7.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), the pileus being chocolate brown to blackish-brown and being fine fibrous to fine scaly (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt-Stohn, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal des JEC" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="28 - 52" refId="B45" refString="Schmidt-Stohn, G, Brandrud, TE, Dima, B, 2017. Interessante Cortinarius -Funde der Journees europeennes du Cortinaire 2016 in Borgsjoe, Schweden. Journal des JEC 19: 28 - 52" title="Interessante Cortinarius - Funde der Journees europeennes du Cortinaire 2016 in Borgsjoe, Schweden." volume="19" year="2017">Schmidt-Stohn et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. subfuscoperonatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="subfuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. subfuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a sister relationship with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fuscoperonatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="fuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. fuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and was well separated according to the phylogenetic analyses. 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. subfuscoperonatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="subfuscoperonatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">C. subfuscoperonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered as the second species in section 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="section" section="Fuscoperonati">Fuscoperonati</taxonomicName>
.
